  "texts": [
    "The study offers methods for resource allocation optimization in complicated environments, contributing significant insights to the fields of edge computing and AI/ML [15] Optimizing the use of resources increases an organization's competitiveness, profitability, and production.Prescriptive Processing Monitoring (PrPM), which focuses on offering recommendations for specific circumstances to get the best results, including lowering completion or cycle times, is cited in the study as a major achievement in data-driven optimization.",
    "PrPM's emphasis on optimizing individual cases at the expense of the wider effects of decisions on other cases, however, is a major drawback.",
    "Data-driven business process optimization (BPO), on the other hand, seeks to improve process performance as a whole, not simply specific instances.",
    "An example of a business process with two activities and resources www.sciforce.org Citation: Dachepalli.",
    "V, \"Intelligent Resource Allocation in ERP with Machine Learning\" Journal of Artificial intelligence and Machine Learning., 2025, vol. 3, no."
  ]
}